            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-21T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="488" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/12–2045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-21T15:00:00-05:00">December 21, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>742. For your information in discharging Secretary’s instructions; of Dec 20 from
                    Moscow, Dept on Dec 8 made informal representations, <pb facs="0520" n="508" xml:id="pg_508"/> to Iranian Ambassador similar to substance of Embtel 4229,
                    Moscow, Dec 20. In frank and friendly terms, Henderson emphasized apparently
                    urgent need for social and economic reforms in Iran, particularly creation of
                    provincial councils. Representations were based upon desirability of
                    strengthening international position of Iran as enlightened sovereign state.
                    From reaction of Ambassador, Dept assumes that Ala has forwarded Dept views to
                    Iranian Govt.</p>
                <p>Sent to Tehran, repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
